Hi,
On Mon, 13 Mar 2000 00:45:48 -0600, Bill Wendling
<wendling@ganymede.isdn.uiuc.edu> said:
> AAAAAAA!!!!!
> WHY?!?! This is horrid! No longer can I simply reboot my machine but I
> have to use command line options?
No, you either install the command line options via lilo, or you use
modules.  Editing conf.modules once to set your sound module
parameters means that you don't have to worry about the state of the
kernel config files every time you build a new kernel.
